                                         JOHANNESBURG - Limpopo police have arrested three suspects for the alleged murder of a 40-year-old Egyptian man who was reported missing last month It's understood the suspects robbed the victim of his vehicle and killed him at a village outside Groblersdal. Police say they then buried him in a shallow grave, where his body was later exhumed by the police. The stolen car and the tools used in the murder were also recovered. The police's Moatshe Ngoepe said: “Three suspects aged between 24 and 41, where two are husband and wife, will appear before the Motetema Magistrates Court on Monday on charges of murder, robbery and possession of a suspected stolen motor vehicle. Our investigations are still continuing.”